{{Infobox organization | name = Standards Board for Alternative Investments | named_after = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | abbreviation = SBAI | motto = | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = {{start date and age|2008|01}} | founder = | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = Nonprofit | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = [[Standards organization|Setting standards]] | headquarters = [[London]] | location = Somerset House, New Wing, Strand | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = [[Alternative investment]] | membership = | membership_year = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | leader_title = Chairman | leader_name = [[Amelia Fawcett]] | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | expenses = | expenses_year = | staff = | staff_year = | mission = | website = {{URL|www.sbai.org}} | formerly = Hedge Fund Standards Board (HFSB) | footnotes = }}
The '''Standards Board for Alternative Investments''' ('''SBAI'''), formerly known as the '''Hedge Fund Standards Board''', is an international [[Standards organization|standard-setting body]] for the [[alternative investment]] industry and sets the voluntary standard of best practices and practices endorsed by its members. Its primary role is to be the custodian of the Alternative Investment Standards (formerly known as "the Standards"), which are designed to create a "framework of transparency, integrity and good governance" in the way the hedge fund industry operates.<ref name="HFSB001"/><ref name="ar16">{{cite book|title=HFSB Annual Report|date=2016|publisher=Standards Board for Alternative Investments|location=UK}}</ref>
== History == The SBAI originated in June 2007, when a group of leading [[alternative investment]] managers formed the Hedge Fund Working Group to develop industry standards in areas such as disclosure, valuation, risk management, governance, and shareholder conduct..<ref name="HFSB001"/> Founding firms included [[Marshall Wace]], [[Cheyne Capital Management]], [[Man Group]], and [[CQS (Asset Manager)|CQS]].<ref name="ar16"/> In January 2008, the working group was established as a nonprofit, called the Hedge Fund Standards Board (HFSB). Its primary purpose was to oversee what's called the "Standards" (now known as the "Alternative Investment Standards"). At its inception, the board had 14 leading hedge fund managers and was chaired by Sir [[Andrew Large]] to develop the standards.<ref name="large">{{cite web|title=Sir Andrew Large: Advisor to the Board|url=http://www.sbai.org/2016/05/13/sir-andrew-large-advisor-to-the-board/|website=SBAI|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> By 2016 it had almost 200 hedge fund managers and [[institutional investors]] as members; the total assets under management of all members was $3 trillion.<ref name="HFSB002"/> In 2014, the board became an affiliate member of the [[International Organization of Securities Commissions]] (IOSCO) and in 2016 established mutual observer relationship with the [[International Forum of Sovereign Wealth Funds]].<ref name="HFSB003"/>
On July 2011, Dame [[Amelia Fawcett]] was appointed Chair of the SBAI, replacing Andrew Large.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dame Amelia Fawcett DBE|url=http://www.sbai.org/2016/05/12/dame-amelia-fawcett-dbe/|website=SBAI|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> In 2014, SBAI becomes an affiliate member of [[International Organization of Securities Commissions]] (IOSCO) and in 2016 SBAI and [[International Forum of Sovereign Wealth Funds]] (IFSWF) agreed to engage in mutual observership.<ref name="feb18">{{cite book|title=Standards Board for Alternative Investments (SBAI)|date=February 2018|publisher=SBAI|location=London|url=http://www.sbai.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/SBAI-General-Presentation.pdf|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref>
In September 2017 it announced that it was changing its name from HFSB to the SBAI or Standards Board for Alternative Investments (SBAI) to "reflect the evolution of the industry". Specifically, it noted that "managers increasingly offer their investment strategies through a variety of vehicles beyond '[[hedge funds]]', including [[liquid alternatives]], regulated funds, [[Equity co-investment|co-investment vehicles]], drawdown funds, and [[managed accounts]]" while at the same time moving away from "hedge fund" as a term in order to "classify and integrate a diverse array of alternatives strategies by underlying asset class, return profile, market exposure, or liquidity".<ref name="letter">{{cite news|title=Hedge Funds Standards Board (HFSB) Becomes Standards Board for Alternative Investments (SBAI)|url=http://www.sbai.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/HFSB-Press-Release-13-September-2017.pdf|accessdate=9 February 2018|work=Standards Board for Alternative Investments|date=13 September 2017}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Alternative investment]] * [[International standard]] * [[Standards organization]]
