The '''Bibliothèque Louis Notari''' (in [[English language|English]] : ''Louis Notari Library'') is the National library of [[Monaco]], founded in 1909.<ref>{{cite book | title=Encyclopedia of European Peoples | publisher=Infobase Publishing | author=Waldman, Carl | year=2006 | isbn=9781438129181}}</ref> It has been the [[legal deposit]] and [[copyright]] library for [[Monaco]] since 1925. It has more than 400,000 books. It is named for Monegasque writer [[Louis Notari]].

