{{Use British English|date=March 2017}} {{Infobox journal | title = Medical Law Review | cover = | abbreviation = Med. Law Rev. | editor = | discipline = [[Law]] | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1997-present | openaccess = | license = | website = https://academic.oup.com/medlaw/(ISSN)1748-121X | link1 = | link1-name = | ISSN = 0967-0742 | eISSN = | CODEN = | LCCN = | OCLC = }} '''''Medical Law Review''''' ({{ISSN|0967-0742}}) is published by [[Oxford University Press]].<ref>[https://academic.oup.com/medlaw/(ISSN)1748-121X Official website]</ref> It was first published in 1997 and publishes [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] scholarly articles, notes, reports, and book reviews. It is current edited by Hazel Biggs<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.southampton.ac.uk/law/about/staff/hb1e08.page|title=Staff profile, University of Southampton}}</ref> and Suzanne Ost.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lancaster.ac.uk/law/people/suzanne-ost|title=Staff profile, Lancaster University}}</ref> A ranking of UK law journals based on statistical data from the 2001 [[Research Assessment Exercise]] places the Medical Law Review as the leading medical law journal.<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Campbell K, Goodacre A, Little G |title=Ranking of United Kingdom Law Journals: An Analysis of the Research Assessment Exercise 2001 Submissions and Results |journal=Journal of Law and Society |volume=33 |pages=335–63 |year=2006 |url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1467-6478.2006.00362.x/abstract |doi=10.1111/j.1467-6478.2006.00362.x}}{{subscription needed}}</ref> It is widely regarded as a leading medical law journal.<ref>{{cite book |author= Claudia Carr |date= 2015 |title=Beginning Medical Law |publisher=[[Routledge]] |location=Abingdon, Oxfordshire |pages=1}}</ref>
