'''Soliman's Water''' was a brand of 16th century cosmetic lotion that was marketed as being able to remove blemishes on the skin, such as [[wart]]s, [[Pimple|spots]] and [[freckle]]s. However, the main ingredient of this lotion was [[mercury (element)|mercury]], so it caused side-effects such as severe damage to the skin and loose teeth.<ref>[http://www.chemie.de/lexikon/e/Soliman's_Water Soliman's Water] Encyclopedia of Chemistry</ref>

